# docmanage License

## Chapter 0. Definitions
**Article 0.**

(1) The Licensor is the legal entity owning the copyrighted works / the project

(2) The project, or copyrighted works, are the docmanage GitHub repository

(3) The Licensee (also referred to as "An individual") is the legal entity agreeing to this license 

(4) Commerical use is either:

  (a) The use of a legal entity with the goal of obtaining profits

  (b) The use of a for-profit company with the goal of obtaining profits

  (c) Internal use of a for-profit company 

## Chapter I. Rights of Non-Commercial Use
**Article 1.** An individual may use the source code of the project for:

(1) Learning / Educational use

(2) Expanding upon the project, with or without the intent to contribute

**Article 2.** An individual may use the project's binaries:

(1) To link against them, either statically or dynamically, as long as the derived work / the rest of the project linking against said binaries is also licensed as either:

  (a) Under the GNU AGPL v3 License

  (b) Under this license

(2) For their intended use

## Chapter II. Rights of Commercial Use
**Article 3.** An individual may use the source code of the project for:

(1) Self-learning, or educational use only for themselves

(2) Expanding upon the project, with the intent to contribute

**Article 4.** An individual may not use the source code of the project for:

(1) Wide-spread educational use

(2) Expanding upon the project without the intent to contribute

**Article 5.** An individual may use the project's binaries:

(1) To link against them, either statically or dynamically, as long as the derived work / the rest of the project linking against said binaries is also licensed under this exact license, with the source code remaining open and available to anyone.

(2) For their intended use

## Chapter III. Rights of Distribution
**Article 6.** An individual may redistribute the project's source code, the project's binaries or other copyrighted works unmodified.

**Article 7.** An individual may redistribute the project's source code, the project's binaries or other copyrighted works that have been altered or modified, explicitly stating that they have been modified.

**Article 8.** An individual may not redistribute the project's source code, the project's binaries or other copyrighted works that have or have not been altered or modified without explicitly stating the original author (The Licensor) and the original project (The Project).
